  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChangePass
    This class is the one used to create a window to change the user password.
    CodeVerification  
    CreateEvent
    This class is the one used to create a window that it allows the user to create a new event.
    CreateOrganizerWindow
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows to create a new organizer.
    CreateUserWindow
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows to create a new user.
    EventListItem
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows the user to have an event list.
    EventOrganizerWindow
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows to an organizer to change or administrate one of his events.
    EventWindow
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows to dsiplay all the information of one event.
    ForgottenPassword
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows a user to log in when he forgets the password.
    LanguageManager
    This class is used to manage the different languages supported by the application.
    LogInWindow
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows a user/organizer to log in to the application.
    OrganizerEvents
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows an organizer to have all of his events.
    OrganizerHome
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows an organizer to have a home window where he can access to all of the functionalities of the application.
    PostCreationWindow
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows an organizer to have like a double check of the event he has just created.
    Profile
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows a user/organizer to have a profile with all of his information.
    SavedEventsWindow
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows to scroll, search and choose from all of the events stored in the database.
    UserEventsWindow
    This class is the one used to create a window that allows a user to scroll, search and select from a list of events he previously has chosen from.
